post_text:
WEATHER UPDATE!

Biloxi Public Schools Parents & Students,

Based on the latest advisory for Hurricane Marco, we have made the decision to cancel school for Monday August 24th. This includes distance learning. While the path of the storm has shifted to the west, we do not wish to chance any potential tropical storm winds, storm surge, or flooding. At this time, school is scheduled to resume as normal on Tuesday August 25th. Plans are fluid, so please monitor local media, email, and the school district website for any future changes or updates.

Thank you and stay safe Indian Nation!
text:
WEATHER UPDATE!

Biloxi Public Schools Parents & Students,

Based on the latest advisory for Hurricane Marco, we have made the decision to cancel school for Monday August 24th. This includes distance learning. While the path of the storm has shifted to the west, we do not wish to chance any potential tropical storm winds, storm surge, or flooding. At this time, school is scheduled to resume as normal on Tuesday August 25th. Plans are fluid, so please monitor local media, email, and the school district website for any future changes or updates.

Thank you and stay safe Indian Nation!

June 5 at 9:00 AM ¬∑

Feel Good Friday News: Shout-out to one of our Club Paw members, Adrienne, who is an eleven year old 6th grader at Biloxi Upper Elementary School. This year, due to COVID-19, she had a parade party rather than a large get together for her birthday and rather than receiving gifts, Adrienne asked that her friends and family bring donations for HSSM!

Adrienne raised $100 as well as over 65 pounds of pet food, dog and cat treats, pet toys, paper towels, blankets and pillows for our shelter pets!

Adrienne aspires to be a Vet when she grows up and is very passionate about helping cats and dogs. She has 3 cats of her own and they are all rescues. Keep up the GREAT WORK, Adrienneüëèüëè

post_text: Congrats to the BJHS Teacher(s) of the Month...#BlxIndianNation üëèüèºüëèüèºüëèüèº
shared_text:
Biloxi Junior High School
April 8 at 11:38 AM ¬∑

It is with great pleasure and pride that we announce Biloxi Junior High's Teachers of the Month - the PARENTS and GUARDIANS of BJHS! We all know that educating a child requires a partnership between teachers, administration, parents, and students, but this month the parents of BJHS have been called upon to step up in ways never before asked or expected of them. Our teachers have done an incredible job of navigating the transition to online learning, and it has taken an amazing amount of support from our parents to really make this a success. From communicating with teachers, creating schedules for students, "learning" the curriculum all over again, and maintaining a positive attitude, our parents have earned the honor of Teachers of the Month! Our Indian Nation is blessed in so many ways, and we are grateful and appreciative of our Tribe of Parents!

Our Culinary team and their instructor, Jessica Moss, recently attended the 4th Annual Regional Hospitality & Tourism Workforce Summit hosted by the University of South Alabama and Mississippi Gulf Coast Community College. Students were able to assist Chef Wendy Bosarge from Scarlet Pearl Casino Resort in preparation of their dish which was a rich chocolate brownie with raspberry chocolate truffle filling dipped in a chocolate ganache!
